I dont consider the changes in pets as a &quot;Luclin change&quot;. Mages recently gained power because pets were changed, simple. That was a independent analysis from Luclin. Just analyse how far pets have come and are finally balanced. Epic pets hps went from 3200 ish to 4200 ish. Max hit went from 67 to 77. Hatse cap was increased so BO4 and muzzle work. Pets eat ripostes less. Pets use owner's resists. Pets dont agro mobs. They damage shield faster now. Pet commands works zonewide. On and on and on. And no these aren't Luclin changes, so dont classify them as such.<br>
<br>
What did we get from Luclin. A broken FB skill. Some of the worst AAs, only better than Beastlords (they have none). I mean who came up with this 4 diff elemental types with 18 pts to spend each for almost negligible improvements and they dont stack. Wizards get rare spell drops EER and Garrison nuke. We get a pet heal which until recently (when they added it to burrower and cursed and emperor loot tables) hadnt even dropped on some server since it was so rare from Grieg and even then is hardly ever put to use. We finally get a Improved Invis type spell after much hue and cry at the fan faire. We get invis at lvl 8 and wizards at lvl 16 and we had to BEG for this to put in. Maybe that's what you meant by making out like bandits. Our best class AA is &quot;Quick Summoning&quot;............ so we can drop rods faster, great, followed by &quot;pet hold&quot; which I doubt anyone would contend should have been default given to all pet classes.<br>
<br>
Maybe the rest of you don't think purely from a raiding perspective but that's the only perspective I personally care for and hence freely admit I only speak of and critisize a specific role in the EQ career of a mage. But for some of us, EQ = raids.<br>
<br>
MGB and Turn Summoned. That's all I have to say about Luclin.<br>
